### 2. Implemented Controller Logic

#### Registration ([RegistrationController.java](file:///c:/Users/vivek/Sem%202/Mini-Project/backend/backend/src/main/java/com/EcoBin/backend/controller/RegistrationController.java)):
* **`/api/register/user/verify`**: Verifies if the user's house coordinates exist in the government `House_details` table. If found, checks for existing accounts, performs a zone mapping search (Kottayam vs Ernakulam by matching local body and ward number), stores the partial registered user with a unique `houseId` and mapped `zoneId`, and returns the `houseId`.
* **`/api/register/user/complete`**: Completes registration by updating password, email, and phone number for the `houseId`.
* **`/api/register/worker`**: Checks duplicates, registers a collection worker under `Collection_workers` with a generated alphanumeric worker ID and password, and returns credentials.
* **`/api/register/staff`**: Registers office staff in the same collection under the role `"OFFICE_STAFF"` with a generated ID (`CS-xxxx`) and password.

#### Dual-Role Login ([LoginController.java](file:///c:/Users/vivek/Sem%202/Mini-Project/backend/backend/src/main/java/com/EcoBin/backend/controller/LoginController.java)):
* **`/api/login`**: Accepts a `userId` and `password`. Looks in `Registered_user` first. If matching, returns user details along with schedule statistics from `Collection_Schedule`. Otherwise, looks in `Collection_workers` and returns worker stats (scheduled zone, number of houses, village name, etc.).

